MUL syntax:

    mul dst, src1, src2    // dst = src1 * src2

The buggy line:
    mul x0, x1, x1        // x0 = 6 * 6 = 36  (wrong!)

Fix it so the third operand is x2 (which holds 7):
    mul x0, x1, x2        // x0 = 6 * 7 = 42  ✓

Remember: all three operands must be registers.
You cannot write   mul x0, x1, #7   — immediates aren't allowed in MUL.
